{
  "title": "Buttons",
  "href": "http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/buttons.html",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "<p>A button clearly communicates what action will occur when the user touches it. It consists of text, an image, or both, designed in accordance with your app&#x2019;s color theme.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "article-list",
      "articles": [
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Button types",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>There are three standard types of buttons: </p><ul><li> <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/buttons-floating-action-button.html\">Floating action button</a>: A circular material button that lifts and displays an ink reaction on press.</li><li>Raised button: A typically rectangular material button that lifts and displays ink reactions on press.</li><li>Flat button: A button made of ink that displays ink reactions on press but does not lift.</li></ul>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VUl95QlVMNXJLU3c/components_buttons_usage1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Floating action button</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VbDh6YmNiYVc3SHM/components_buttons_usage2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Raised button</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VNDg3V3ZjU2hsNGc/components_buttons_usage3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Flat button</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0Vb0pRdVVtOElwTHM/components_buttons_usage4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of a floating action button</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VTEp2XzZSTzVBMUU/components_buttons_usage5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of a raised button </p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VaDdZWXpLXzNicjg/components_buttons_usage6.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of a flat button</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Choosing a button style depends on the primacy of the button, the number of containers on screen, and the screen layout. </p><p><strong>Function:</strong>&#xA0;Is it important and ubiquitous enough to be a floating action button? </p><p><strong>Dimension:</strong>&#xA0;Choose raised or flat depending on the container it will be in and how many z-space layers you have on screen. There should not be many layers of objects on the screen.</p><p><strong>Layout:</strong>&#xA0;Use primarily one type of button per container. Only mix button types when you have a good reason to, such as emphasizing an important function.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7RHFUU2dFdmMtcm8/components_buttons_usage_main.png"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Choosing button style"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Usage",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Use flat buttons on dialogs to unify the button action with the dialog content.</p><ul><li>Dialog text padding: 24dp </li><li>Dialog button container height: 52dp</li><li>Dialog buttons: 8dp padding from container edges, aligned to the right of container (for LTR scripts)</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsSXNCRmd0aE5WWWs/components_buttons_usage_dialogs1.png"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Buttons in dialogs"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsUUY1MHRaUDdDTGs/components_buttons_usage_dialogs2.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\"></div><p>Flat buttons in dialogs </p><p><strong>Dialog buttons</strong><br>Button height: 36dp<br>Button top margin: 24dp<br>Button padding: 8dp<br>Button alignment: Right edge for LTR scripts<br>Button width: Varies based on button text length</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsU1A0aDJMMGhQRjQ/components_buttons_keyline1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Examples of flat buttons in dialogs </p><p><strong>Button</strong><br>Height: 36dp<br>Minimum width: 64dp<br>Touch target height: 48dp<br>Horizontal margin: 8dp<br>Horizontal padding: 8dp </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Choose raised or flat buttons depending on your layout. Add padding around flat buttons so the user can easily find them.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsdU42S2h4QnJMZVE/components_buttons_usage_buttons1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of flat button </p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQscGRSZUU4a0lxc0U/components_buttons_usage_buttons2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of raised button </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Buttons inline"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>If your app requires actions to be persistent and readily available to the user, consider using the floating action button. </p><p>Alternatively, consider persistent footer buttons, which are also easily accessible.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7Ukt1TFRVUlgxY1k/components_buttons_keyline2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Persistent footer buttons are 48dp tall. </p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQseU1yM2R4VmhFamc/components_buttons_usage_buttons4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Example of persistent footer buttons</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Persistent footer buttons"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Never use raised buttons within persistent button areas.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7SDNoT21jRWJkZG8/components_buttons_keyline3.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Don&apos;t.</div>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>With the addition of a divider, a persistent footer button can also be used for scrollable dialogs.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQscWJWbkVHaDcyNEE/components_buttons_usage_buttons5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Persistent footer button in dialog</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsUnd1MlhhVUw1Z28/components_buttons_usage_buttons6.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Persistent footer button in scrollable dialog</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Flat & raised buttons",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Raised buttons add dimension to mostly flat layouts. They emphasize functions on busy or wide spaces.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsR0hib1ExN21wWjA/components_buttons_main5.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Use raised buttons to give more prominence to actions in layouts with a lot of varying content.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsX0xZMnFkR1ZOVmc/components_buttons_main6.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Raised buttons can even help delineate sections of content on a page.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Raised buttons"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsMF8xdDNDNUc0Zk0/components_buttons_main7.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Do.</div><p>Raised buttons stand out more than flat buttons.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsZk0xMExROVpzLWs/components_buttons_main8.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Don&apos;t.</div><p>Don&#x2019;t use flat buttons in UIs where they would be difficult to see.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Use flat buttons for toolbars and dialogs to avoid excessive layering.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsWVJfOVpiVHYtZ00/components_buttons_main9.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Flat buttons are appropriate in dialogs.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsckpmZTBwSmh1VzQ/components_buttons_main10.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Flat buttons minimize distraction from content.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Flat buttons"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsTDEwRlFpUmZtVm8/components_buttons_main11.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Do.</div><p>Correct use of flat buttons.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B6Okdz75tqQsS2U2VUVCOVFaRlU/components_buttons_main12.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Don&apos;t.</div><p>The raised buttons here are too heavy.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Flat buttons are printed on material. They do not lift, but fill with color on press.</p><p>Raised buttons behave like a piece of material resting on another sheet &#x2013; they lift and fill with color on press. </p><p>Button text should be capitalized in languages that have capitalization. For other languages, colored text on flat buttons distinguishes them from normal text. </p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7SnA4Umw3S0pfNWs/components_buttons_main13.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Flat Light/Light theme</div><p>Minimum width: 88dp<br>Height: 36dp<br>Pressed: 40% #999999<br>Disabled text: 26% #000000</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7bEFqalRSeUJkbEU/components_buttons_main14.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Flat Dark/Dark theme</div><p>Minimum width: 88dp<br>Height: 36dp<br>Pressed: 25% #CCCCCC<br>Disabled text: 30% #FFFFFF</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Flat and raised button states"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3VDJmNWRVMFhyQUE/components_buttons_focus_flat.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Flat buttons with 12% opacity on focus </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7WlduMk1kbTRzQWc/components_buttons_main15.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Raised Light/Light theme</div><p>Minimum width: 88dp <br>Height: 36dp <br>Disabled text: 26% #000000<br>Disabled button: 12% #000000</p><p>Focused:12% #000000 shade over the color</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bx4BSt6jniD7UTh2dExpSlRVWVU/components_buttons_main16.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Raised Dark/Dark theme</div><p>Minimum width: 88dp <br>Height: 36dp <br>Normal color: 500 <br>Pressed color: 700 <br>Disabled text: 30% #FFFFFF <br>Disabled button: 12% #FFFFFF</p><p>Focused:12% #000000 shade over the color</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Accessibility</h4><p>To ensure usability for people with disabilities, give buttons a height of 36dp and give touchable targets a minimum height of 48dp.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3LTRtTEtDdVpzYWM/components_buttons_keyline4.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\"></div><p>Button height: 36dp<br>Touchable target height: 48dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Button Elevation</h4><p>Raised buttons have a default elevation of 2dp.</p><p>On desktop, raised buttons can gain this elevation on hover.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B8olV15J7abPZm1EakJMZWxSdXc/components_buttons_main17.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Dark/Light</strong>&#xA0;<strong>theme</strong></p><p>Minimum width: 64dp <br>Height: 36dp <br>Z-depth: 0dp<br>Disabled text: 30% #FFFFFF<br>Disabled button: 12% #FFFFFF</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Density</h4><p>When mouse and keyboard are the primary input methods, button measurements can be slightly reduced to accommodate dense UIs. </p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B8olV15J7abPM3QyLXVkSnpJOEE/components_buttons_main18.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Default Button</div>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B8olV15J7abPdHFuQ2VaejdBQ3c/components_buttons_main19.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Dense Button</div>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B8olV15J7abPeUpjMndNN29HMTQ/components_buttons_main20.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Button text: 14pt Roboto medium<br>Button height: 36dp<br>Button text left and right padding: 16dp</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B8olV15J7abPZ1hOcnRjRFhvZ2s/components_buttons_main21.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Button text: 13pt Roboto medium<br>Button height: 32dp<br>Button text left and right padding: 16dp</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "video",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3T7oTWa3HiFSTNhRndpWXBwRDA/components-buttons-flatbuttons.webm",
                      "caption": "<p>Flat buttons</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "video",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3T7oTWa3HiFRmZDbzdkSEp0ZEk/components-buttons-raisedbuttons.webm",
                      "caption": "<p>Raised buttons</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Buttons in motion"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Toggle buttons",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Toggle buttons may be used to group related options. Arrange layout and spacing to convey that certain toggle buttons are part of a group.</p><p>Focus and pressed states may reinforce that toggles are part of a group.  For example, when one button segment is focused, focus may be displayed simultaneously on the rest of the segment.</p><p>Toggle button requirements:</p><ul><li>Have at least three toggle buttons in a group</li><li>Label buttons with text, an icon, or both</li></ul><p>The following combinations are recommended:</p><ul><li>Multiple and unselected</li><li>Exclusive and unselected</li><li>Exclusive only   </li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3V2JKWk9EbzFaMjg/components_buttons_togglebuttons1.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Exclusive selection</div><p>Text justification toggle buttons present options for left, right, center, full, and justified text &#xA0;with only one item available for selection at a time. Selecting one option deselects any other.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3NzNSMUpjSkhtdXM/components_buttons_togglebuttons2.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Multiple selection</div><p>Logically-grouped options, like Bold, Italic, and Underline, allow multiple options to be selected.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3ckVldVFCWE1INnc/components_buttons_togglebuttons3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>No options are selected</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3am5aV3VnUHFhQW8/components_buttons_togglebuttons4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>One option is selected</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Icons are appropriate for toggle buttons that allow a single choice to be selected or deselected, such as adding or removing a star to an item.</p><p>They are best located in app bars, toolbars, action buttons or toggles.</p><p>Icon toggles may display bounded or unbounded ink <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/animation/responsive-interaction.html#responsive-interaction-surface-reaction\">surface reaction</a> ripples beyond their touch-target bounds.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B_udO5B8pzrzdXVuTlBoOTBjcU0/components_buttons_other1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Icon toggles in normal, hover, focused, pressed, and inactive states  </p>"
